wikipedia_page.main: Theodore Rathbone Hubback (17 December 1872 in Liverpool, England – 1942 in Malaya) was an English engineer, conservationist and author in what is now Malaysia.  He was instrumental in the formation of the King George V National Park in 1938, now known as Taman Negara. A wicket-keeper, he played first-class cricket for Lancashire in 1892.
